whereas.text:
Whereas the Republic of Korea and the United States enjoy
			 a warm friendship built on a commitment to security, joint economic
			 development, cultural exchange, and the democratic process;

Whereas in the years after the Korean War, the Republic of
			 Korea developed its civil society and built a vibrant democracy that is the
			 basis for regional stability and an engine of global economic growth;

Whereas the Korean American community is a great reminder
			 of the shared bonds of the people of the Republic of Korea and the United
			 States forged by 60 years of friendship;
